text.tspan: Etienne Kneuss, Viktor Kuncak and Philippe Suter
Laboratory of Automated Reasonning and Analysis

flowRoot.flowPara: Insane is a combination of a pointer analysis with a memory effect analysis for the Scala prog-ramming language. Our analysis is based on abs-tract interpretation, it is inter-procedural and flow sensitive. The analysis, aimed at higher order programs, computes compositional sum-maries using a very expressive representation of effects and does not require annotations.
